text: Jupiter LXI, also known as , is a moon of Jupiter. It was found by a team of astronomers led by Brett J. Gladman, et al. in 2003.IAUC 8125: S/2003 J 19 and S/2003 J 20 2003 April 30 (discovery)MPEC 2003-G64: S/2003 J 19 2003 April 12 (discovery and ephemeris) Jupiter LXI is about 2 kilometres in diameter, and orbits Jupiter at an average distance of 22,709,000 km in 699.125 days, at an inclination of 165° to the ecliptic (164° to Jupiter's equator), with an orbital eccentricity of 0.1961. It belongs to the Carme group, made up of non- spherical retrograde moons orbiting Jupiter at a distance ranging between 23,000,000 and 24,000,000 km and at an inclination of about 165°. == References == Category:Jupiter's moons
